        >> In Java, operators are special symbols or keywords used to perform operations on variables and values.

<|> 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐎𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
      >> It supoorts a wide range of operators, which can be categorized into different groups based on their functionality.

          :: Arithmetic Operator
          :: Assignment operator
          :: Logical operator
          :: Bitwise operator
          :: Comparison operator
          :: Unary operator

-------------------><-----------------------><--------------------

 |< 𝟏 >| 𝐀𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐡𝐦𝐞𝐭𝐢𝐜 𝐎𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Used to perform basic mathematical operations.

 |< 𝟐 >| 𝐀𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Used to assign values to variables.

 |< 𝟑 >| 𝐋𝐨𝐠𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐥 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Used to combine conditional statements.

 |< 𝟒 >| 𝐁𝐢𝐭𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐞 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Operate on binary representations of numbers.

 |< 𝟓 >| 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐨𝐧 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Used to compare two values. They return either True or False.
         >> Known as Relational Operator.

|< 𝟔 >| 𝐔𝐧𝐚𝐫𝐲 𝐎𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 <|>
         >> Unary operators work on a single operand and perform operations 
         >> such as incrementing, decrementing, negating, or inverting a value. 



